SKHR Server, API version 1.0:
New SKHR User Flow:
register (email, password, device id, ) - return "user_id"
verify (verification code, user id) - return "token"

New Third party (facebook, google) User Flow:
login (fb_id, fb_link, token, token_expiry, device_id, verified) - return "user_id" 


POST /api/v1/user/register HTTP/1.1
json: $data = {







}
return $data = {







}
POST /api/v1/user/login HTTP/1.1
receive $data = {







}
return $data = {







}



---------------------------- Server Configurations --------------------------------
Configure the http server document root:

/etc/apache2/sites-available/default

	DocumentRoot /home/ronend/skhr/code/SKHR_Server
	<Directory /home/ronend/skhr/code/SKHR_Server/>
	    Options Indexes FollowSymLinks MultiViews
	    AllowOverride ALL
	    Order allow,deny
	    allow from all
	</Directory>

/etc/apache2/apache2.conf
	
	AccessFileName .htaccess

-------------- PEAR installation - Sending Mail via Gmail accountn --------------
sudo pear install Mail-1.2.0
sudo pear install Net_SMTP
fix for pear: https://github.com/centralnic/php-epp/commit/e15db31f72b1e3d1ff8532659190fbd8af70bbee

